Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: NameThatColor
Version: 1.0.1
Summary: Find human-readable color names for hex values
Home-page: http://github.com/jdodds/py-name-that-color
Author: Jeremiah Dodds
Author-email: jeremiah.dodds@gmail.com
License: LICENSE.txt
Download-URL: http://github.com/jdodds/py-name-that-color/downloads
Description: This is a little utility to give you the "human readable" color name given a hex
        value. Heavily based (one might even just call it a port...) on
        [ntc.js](http://chir.ag/projects/ntc/) by Chirag Mehta.
        
        Usage
        =====
        
        + As a library:
        
            \>\>\> from NameThatColor import NameThatColor
            
            \>\>\> Namer = NameThatColor()
            
            \>\>\> Namer.name('FFFFFF')
            
            Match(hex_value='#FFFFFF', name='White', exact=True, original='#FFFFFF')
            
            \>\>\> Namer.name('#FFFFFF')
            
            Match(hex_value='#FFFFFF', name='White', exact=True, original='#FFFFFF')
            
            \>\>\> Namer.name('aabbcc')
            
            Match(hex_value='#ADBED1', name='Casper', exact=False, original='#AABBCC')
        + As a program:
            $ namethatcolor ffffff
            
            {"match_hex": "#FFFFFF", "match_name": "White"}
        
